messages.text: So, what will you do if you have the baby?
How will you take care of it?
I don‚Äôt know ‚Äî I haven‚Äôt thought that far out yet.
Honestly, I don‚Äôt even know if I *actually* want to keep it.
But for once, I just want to feel like I have a choice.
Of course you have a choice, Angie.
Is there something else I should know?
Cameras flash. Angie smiles to the parade crowd.
No. I‚Äôm just a little freaked out.
At 2 a.m., after the Inauguration is over, Angie gets another text from Will.
Or are you at some fancy party? üòù
Haha, just got back from the last fancy party.
This is supposed to be our house, but it feels like I‚Äôm staying at a hotel.
Massive. I have this huge four-poster bed.
Mom put up these antique-y drapes around my balcony. It overlooks the garden.
Did she at least let you put up your Ruth Bader Ginsburg poster?
Yeah, but I had to compromise‚Ä¶
So now it‚Äôs in this huge frame that supposedly belonged to Thomas Jefferson.
Why‚Äôd you stop talking to me?
Classes, work‚Ä¶it was hard to keep up.
Well, at least we‚Äôre talking now.
You have a human growing inside of you.
Have you ever thought about it?
What you would do if you got someone pregnant?
It wouldn‚Äôt really be my choice, would it?
What if she wanted to keep it?
Not that I‚Äôve had the opportunity to make this a possibility, but‚Ä¶
I‚Äôd support the kid the best I could. He‚Äôd be my responsibility too.

What will people say about him when they find out I‚Äôm knocked up?

Angie‚Ä¶you can‚Äôt take on all of that responsibility.
Your dad chose to be the president.

YOU get to choose whether you have this baby or not.
You guess? What does that mean?
Fine, you don‚Äôt have to tell me, but please, keep talking to me.
Tell me more about your room.
What other horrible decorations did your mom put up? üôà
Um‚Ä¶there‚Äôs a giant metal peacock by the fireplace?
See, I always suspected the White House had a giant metal peacock problem.
But I didn‚Äôt really believe it until just now.
Still hacking into the school‚Äôs computer system for fun?

Says she‚Äôs gonna stay clean this time.

But seriously, are you guys okay?
You wouldn‚Äôt believe the number of trust fund kids failing their classes.

If it helps, I‚Äôm much better now that I‚Äôm talking to you.
Angie‚Äôs phone dings with a new text from Kyle. Angie switches over to her text chain with him.
